changelog.comment: Fixed URL formatting. Fixed incorrect GenPept and Uniprot IDs (pointed to Amycolatopsis orientalis instead of balhimycina).

reactions.description: Installs a biaryl ether bond on the balhiycin precursor. The reaction might be less specific than depicted in the reaction SMARTS. There is no detailed study on the specificity so far. The reaction occurs probably while the precursor peptide backbone is bound to the NRPS as shown for the closely related vancomycin biosynthesis (10.1002/ANIE.200461278).
Introduces the second crosslink (biaryl ether) between hpg5 and dhpg7 of the balhimycin precursor.
